title: The unique extremal QC mapping and uniqueness of Hahn-Banach extensions
abstract:
Let χ be an essentialy bounded complex valued measurable function defined on the unit disc Δ, and let Λ_χ be the corresponding linear functional on the space B of analytic
L^1-integrable functions.
An outline of proof of main steps of the following is given: If |χ| is a constant function in Δ, then the uniqueness of Hahn-Banach extension of Λ_χ, from B to L^1, when ||Λ_ χ|| = ||χ||∞, implies that χ is the unique complex dilatation.
We give a short review of some related results.
